results.name: Array where n-th row contains the primes < n and coprime to n.
comment: Array's n-th row contains A048865(n) terms.
These are the primes in row n >= 3 of A038566 (smallest positive restricted residue system modulo n). - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Jan 18 2017
link: Michael De Vlieger, Table of n, a(n) for n = 3..16603 (rows 3 <= n <= 400).
example: Row 9 is [2, 5, 7], since 2, 5 and 7 are the primes < 9 and coprime to 9.
mathematica: f[l_] := Block[{n}, n = Length[l] + 1; Return[Append[l, Select[Range[n - 1], PrimeQ[ # ] && Mod[n, # ] > 0 &]]];]; Flatten[Nest[f, {}, 24]] (* _Ray Chandler_, Dec 26 2005 *)
Table[Complement[Prime@ Range@ PrimePi@ n, FactorInteger[n][[All, 1]]], {n, 3, 23}] // Flatten (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Sep 04 2017 *)
program: def a(n): return [i for i in primerange(1, n) if gcd(i, n)==1]
for n in range(3, 24): print(a(n)) # _Indranil Ghosh_, Apr 27 2017
